Repositories

Mainline DTS and DTSI files for ST
STM32 seems to have been 32 bit until the STM32MP2 series which are 64 bit...
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm/boot/dts/st
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm64/boot/dts/st

ST
https://github.com/STMicroelectronics

Mainline DTS (Device Tree Source) file for the NXP i.MX 8 M Plus on the Debix Model A SoM (System on Module) mounted on the Debix Model A SoM I/O Board (product number BMB-08)
This is in the freescale directory - named before the Freescale NXP merger.
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mp-debix-som-a-bmb-08.dts

Mainline DTSI (Device Tree Structure Include) file for the NXP i.MX 8 M Plus on the Debix Model A SoM (System on Module) only:
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mp-debix-som-a.dtsi

Mainline DTS (Device Tree Source) file for the NXP i.MX 8 M Plus on the Debix Model A SBC (Single Board Computer)
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mp-debix-model-a.dts

DTOs (Device Tree Overlays) for the Debix 200a camera, Debix 500a camera and IMX335 image sensor for the i.MX 8 M Plus:
Note that these were written for the Debix Model A SBC so may need to be adjusted for the Debix Model A SoM and Debix Model A SoM I/O board.
https://git.uk.ideasonboard.com/camera/dt-overlays/src/branch/main/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale

DTS (Device Tree Strucure) for the official NXP i.MX 8 M Plus evaluation board.
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mp-evk.dts
Note that several DTSI and DTSO files with names beginning imx8mp-evk are available for different configurations in the freescale directory - named before the Freescale NXP merger:
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/

Mainline DTSI (Device Tree Structure Include) for the i.MX 8 M Plus chip
This is in the freescale directory - named before the Freescale NXP merger.
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mp.dtsi

